tors in brazil vale is the largest producer of iron ore and nickel in the world vale also produces manganese ferroalloys copper bauxite potash kaolin and cobalt the company also currently operates nine hydroelectricity plants and a large network of railroads ships and ports used to transport its products contents  current operations  ownership structure  mining business  logistics  railroads  ports and container terminals  brazil  malaysia  ships  energy  rebranding  history  privatization in   sale of wood pulp businesses  sale of steel businesses  acquisitions of brazilian iron ore companies  acquisition of caemi and acquisition and partial disposition of mbr  diversification into nonferrous metals coal and phosphate  controversies  criticism  references  bibliography  external links current operationsedit although the companys primary operations are in brazil vale has operations in  countries which are detailed below and on the companys website ownership structureedit the company is listed on the stock exchanges of são paulo new york city paris hong kong and madrid the brazilian government owns  golden shares that give it control over certain actions including a liquidation or change in principal office mining businessedit vales carajás iron mine pará  nasa satellite photo iron ore vale is the worlds largest iron ore producer sales of iron ore fines and pellets represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  million metric tonnes of iron ore fines and  million metric tonnes of iron ore pellets vales mariana hub was the th largest iron ore mining center in the world in  with an output of  million metric tonnes vales serra sull  sd is the largest mining reserve in the world the companys iron ore mines are primarily in brazil nickel vale is the worlds largest nickel producer sales of nickel represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  metric tonnes of nickel the company owns nickel mines in canada indonesia new caledonia and brazil fertilizer products primarily phosphates and nitrogen sales of fertilizer products represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  million metric tonnes of fertilizer products copper sales of copper concentrate represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  metric tonnes of copper the company owns copper mines in brazil canada chile and zambia manganese and alloys sales of manganese and alloys represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  million metric tonnes of manganese and alloys coal sales of coal represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  million metric tonnes of coal the company owns coal mines in australia and mozambique logisticsedit railroadsedit from  to  vale invested more than  billion on the acquisition of over  locomotives and around  freight cars those locomotives were primarily for iron ore transportation but some were for regular cargo some of the locomotives purchased were secondhand for refurbishment but at least  of the locomotives acquired were new ones of the model emd sdm each one costing about  million after those investments vale became the owner of over  locomotives and more than  freight cars vale owns the concession of three brazilian railways vitória a minas railroad efvm ferrovia centroatlântica fca and carajás railroad efc ferrovia centroatlântica and vitória a minas railroads vitória a minas railroad  vale operates under a year contract this  km  mm  ft  ⁄ in railroad which is used to transport iron from the iron quadrangle in minas gerais to the port of tubarão in the state of espírito santo  the concession expires in  this railroad also carried  million passengers in  carajás railroad  the concession of this  km  mm  ft  in gauge railroad also expires in  it links carajás iron ore mines in the state of pará to ponta da madeira port terminal in the state of maranhão vale operates a train of  km and  cars on this railroad ferrovia centroatlântica  vale controls this railroad through the subsidiary fca as it is shown on the vales operations map above this  km  mm  ft  ⁄ in railroad extends through  brazilian states this railroad originally belonged to the rffsa vales concession of this railroad expires in  vale also has a stake in railway operators in mozambique and malawi ports and container terminalsedit braziledit port of tubarão  vale owns and operates this port located in vitória brazil in the state of espirito santo its the largest iron ore embarking port in the world around  million metric tons of iron ore  of the companys annual production are shipped through this port ponta da madeira  located in the state of maranhão it ships around  million metric tons mostly of iron ore but also of manganese and copper for the company it is being upgraded for the sd project port of sepetiba  vale operates two maritime terminals in the port of sepetiba area located in the state of rio de janeiro together they ship around  million metric tons of iron ore vale also operates port terminals in the state of sergipe and two others in the state of espirito santo malaysiaedit teluk rubiah maritime terminal trmt  a state of the art maritime terminal in the state of perak operates distribution centre for iron ore caters for asia pacific shipsedit vale has also entered the shipping business by ordering  very large ore carriers vloc to transport iron ore between south america and asia these metre  ft  dwt ships are the longest and largest dry bulk carriers in the world the first ship vale brasil was delivered in march  energyedit vales energy business is focused at power production to fulfill the needs of its mining operations as well as supplying the general brazilian power grid in  it consumed  twh of electrical power accounting for  of brazils total consumption in that yearcitation needed vale has participation in  hydroelectric plants with  of these located in the state of minas gerais vales investment in hydroelectric power plants totals  million the company also plans to build a  mw thermoeletric power plant in the state of pará vales hydroeletric power plants name location production capacity vales ownership vales investment start of operations aimorés minas gerais  mw   million july  candonga minas gerais  mw   million september  capim branco i minas gerais  mw   million february  capim branco ii minas gerais  mw   million may  estreito tocantins  mw   million august  funil minas gerais  mw   million december  igarapava minas gerais  mw   million january  porto estrela minas gerais  mw   million september  vale also operates hydroelectric plants in canada and indonesia rebrandingedit in november  the company retired the name cvrd in favour of simplified company name of vale and rebranded historyedit founded as companhia vale do rio doce widely known as cvrd prior to  in english doce river valley company was founded in itabira minas gerais by the brazilian federal government on  june  one year later the vitória a minas railroad was inaugurated the s marked companhia vale do rio doce’s entry into the global iron ore market after the companys minerailroadport complex was modernized and iron ore prices doubled at first sales were mostly to the united states but exports to europe increased over the course of the decade in  the company inaugurated in espirito santo the port of tubarão which was to become the most important port for cvrd and is still used to export iron ore mined from the iron quadrangle in minas gerais the company acquired a majority interest in the carajás mine with over  billion tonnes of iron ore in reserves in  in  vale became the worlds biggest exporter of iron ore a title which it still holds today in  vale began to diversify after it started to produce aluminium in rio de janeiro in the mid s profits increased considerably under the leadership of eliezer batista father of eike batista in  vale started to explore the carajás mine in the state of pará just after the  mm  ft  in gauge carajás railroad was opened in