although the companys primary operations are in brazil vale has operations in  countries which are detailed below and on the companys website ownership structureedit the company is listed on the stock exchanges of são paulo new york city paris hong kong and madrid the brazilian government owns  golden shares that give it control over certain actions including a liquidation or change in principal office mining businessedit vales carajás iron mine pará  nasa satellite photo iron ore vale is the worlds largest iron ore producer sales of iron ore fines and pellets represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  million metric tonnes of iron ore fines and  million metric tonnes of iron ore pellets vales mariana hub was the th largest iron ore mining center in the world in  with an output of  million metric tonnes vales serra sull  sd is the largest mining reserve in the world the companys iron ore mines are primarily in brazil nickel vale is the worlds largest nickel producer sales of nickel represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  metric tonnes of nickel the company owns nickel mines in canada indonesia new caledonia and brazil fertilizer products primarily phosphates and nitrogen sales of fertilizer products represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  million metric tonnes of fertilizer products copper sales of copper concentrate represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  metric tonnes of copper the company owns copper mines in brazil canada chile and zambia manganese and alloys sales of manganese and alloys represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  million metric tonnes of manganese and alloys coal sales of coal represented  of total company revenues in  in  vale sold  million metric tonnes of coal the company owns coal mines in australia and mozambique logisticsedit railroadsedit from  to  vale invested more than  billion on the acquisition of over  locomotives and around  freight cars those locomotives were primarily for iron ore transportation but some were for regular cargo some of the locomotives purchased were secondhand for refurbishment but at least  of the locomotives acquired were new ones of the model emd sdm each one costing about  million after those investments vale became the owner of over  locomotives and more than  freight cars vale owns the concession of three brazilian railways vitória a minas railroad efvm ferrovia centroatlântica fca and carajás railroad efc ferrovia centroatlântica and vitória a minas railroads vitória a minas railroad  vale operates under a year contract this  km  mm  ft  ⁄ in railroad which is used to transport iron from the iron quadrangle in minas gerais to the port of tubarão in the state of espírito santo  the concession expires in  this railroad also carried  million passengers in  carajás railroad  the concession of this  km  mm  ft  in gauge railroad also expires in  it links carajás iron ore mines in the state of pará to ponta da madeira port terminal in the state of maranhão vale operates a train of  km and  cars on this railroad ferrovia centroatlântica  vale controls this railroad through the subsidiary fca as it is shown on the vales operations map above this  km  mm  ft  ⁄ in railroad extends through  brazilian states this railroad originally belonged to the rffsa vales concession of this railroad expires in  vale also has a stake in railway operators in mozambique and malawi ports and container terminalsedit braziledit port of tubarão  vale owns and operates this port located in vitória brazil in the state of espirito santo its the largest iron ore embarking port in the world around  million metric tons of iron ore  of the companys annual production are shipped through this port ponta da madeira  located in the state of maranhão it ships around  million metric tons mostly of iron ore but also of manganese and copper for the company it is being upgraded for the sd project port of sepetiba  vale operates two maritime terminals in the port of sepetiba area located in the state of rio de janeiro together they ship around  million metric tons of iron ore vale also operates port terminals in the state of sergipe and two others in the state of espirito santo malaysiaedit teluk rubiah maritime terminal trmt  a state of the art maritime terminal in the state of perak operates distribution centre for iron ore caters for asia pacific shipsedit vale has also entered the shipping business by ordering  very large ore carriers vloc to transport iron ore between south america and asia these metre  ft  dwt ships are the longest and largest dry bulk carriers in the world the first ship vale brasil was delivered in march  energyedit vales energy business is focused at power production to fulfill the needs of its mining operations as well as supplying the general brazilian power grid in  it consumed  twh of electrical power accounting for  of brazils total consumption in that yearcitation needed vale has participation in  hydroelectric plants with  of these located in the state of minas gerais vales investment in hydroelectric power plants totals  million the company also plans to build a  mw thermoeletric power plant in the state of pará vales hydroeletric power plants name location production capacity vales ownership vales investment start of operations aimorés minas gerais  mw   million july  candonga minas gerais  mw   million september  capim branco i minas gerais  mw   million february  capim branco ii minas gerais  mw   million may  estreito tocantins  mw   million august  funil minas gerais  mw   million december  igarapava minas gerais  mw   million january  porto estrela minas gerais  mw   million september  vale also operates hydroelectric plants in canada and indonesia rebrandingedit in november  the company retired the name cvrd in favour of simplified company name of vale and rebranded historyedit founded as companhia vale do rio doce widely known as cvrd prior to  in english doce river valley company was founded in itabira minas gerais by the brazilian federal government on  june  one year later the vitória a minas railroad was inaugurated the s marked companhia vale do rio doce’s entry into the global iron ore market after the companys minerailroadport complex was modernized and iron ore prices doubled at first sales were mostly to the united states but exports to europe increased over the course of the decade in  the company inaugurated in espirito santo the port of tubarão which was to become the most important port for cvrd and is still used to export iron ore mined from the iron quadrangle in minas gerais the company acquired a majority interest in the carajás mine with over  billion tonnes of iron ore in reserves in  in  vale became the worlds biggest exporter of iron ore a title which it still holds today in  vale began to diversify after it started to produce aluminium in rio de janeiro in the mid s profits increased considerably under the leadership of eliezer batista father of eike batista in  vale started to explore the carajás mine in the state of pará just after the  mm  ft  in gauge carajás railroad was opened in  ponta madeira port terminal which is still used to export iron ore mined at the carajás mine was inaugurated in the state of maranhão in march  vale sa choose a commodities industry veteran fabio schvartsman as chief executive officer schvartsman was ceo of klabin sa brazils largest paper and cardboard producer for the past six years privatization in edit in may  despite protests by vale employees and some politicians the brazilian government auctioned a  interest in the company which was sold for r billion us billion the largest interest purchased was a  stake purchased by brazilian steel company companhia siderúrgica nacional sale of wood pulp businessesedit in  vale sold its cenibra wood pulp business for us million to focus on mining and logistics in  vale sold  acres of land and the eucalyptus forests thereon related to its wood pulp business for r million sale of steel businessesedit in  the company sold its stake in açominas to gerdau in exchange for preferred shares in gerdau in  vale sold its stake in companhia siderúrgica nacional for r million in  vale sold its stake in cst to arcelor for us million in  vale sold its interest in siderar to ternium for us million in  the company sold  shares in usiminas for or r million in  the company sold the majority of its stake in usiminas in  the company sold its remaining stake in usiminas acquisitions of brazilian iron ore companiesedit in may  the company acquired sociomex owner of the gongo sôco mine with proven reserves of approximately  million tons in may  the company also acquired a controlling interest in samitri one of the biggest pelletizing companies of brazil in april  the company acquired ferteco then the third largest brazilian producer of iron ore with a production capacity of  million tonnes per year in  the company acquired rio verde mineracao for  million acquisition of caemi and acquisition and partial disposition of mbredit on  april  vale offered to pay mitsui us million for  of the common shares and us million for  of the preferred stock in caemi caemi owned mbr brazils second largest iron ore producer mining over  million tonnes per year the acquisition was approved by european regulators subject to conditions in september  vale purchased an additional stake in caemi from mitsui for us million on  january  the company announced a stock swap merger to acquire the interest caemi that it did not already own in  increased its ownership in mbr by purchasing additional interests from mitsui for us million also in  vale announced that it will lease the shares of mbr that it did not already own from their  japanese shareholders for a year period the agreement required the company to pay a total of us million in  and us million annually for a year period and gave it total control of mbr in  vale announced the sale of a  interest in mbr for r billion diversification into nonferrous metals coal and phosphateedit in  vale increased its copper mining operations by purchasing the sossego mine in carajas in northern brazil for  million in  vale acquired canico resource owner of a nickel mine in brazil after increasing its offer to  million in october  vale acquired canadianbased nickel producer inco for  billion including  billion in cash and the assumption of  billion in debt to gain approval from canadian authorities vale promised to continue investments in canada and not layoff people for  years after closing in  vale made a major entry into coal mining by acquiring amci holdings australia for au million in  vale launched a public offer to acquire fertilizer and copper producer paranapanema in  vale acquired a controlling interest in fosfertil via a series of transactions in june  jason chenier and jordan fram were killed at the  foot level of the frood mine near sudbury ontario in  the company sold its aluminum business to norsk hydro in a us billion transaction in july  vale sold its ferromanganese plants in europe to glencore for  million in  vale announced the sale of coal assets in mozambique to mitsui in a  million transaction in  vale sold its interest in fosbrasil sa a manufacturer of phosphatebased products in  the company announced that it would sell a  interest in gold produced from its salobo mine located in brazil to silver wheaton for us million in  the company entered into a letter of intent to sell bauxite assets to norsk hydro on  november  a dam collapsed at the samarco mining site coowned by vale and bhp billiton the accident resulted in  deaths and massive environmental contamination activities at the mine were suspended and the companies agreed to pay compensation of r billion us billion on  november  vale announced that it planned to reduce its budget for capital expenditures from us billion in  to us billion in  with further reductions to us– billion by  controversiesedit criticismedit a village flooded in the bento rodrigues dam disaster  the dam was a property of samarco a joint venture between vale and bhp billiton vale was elected as the corporation with the most contempt for the environment and human rights in the world during a january  vote organized by the public eye the choice was made by public vote and vale received  votes referencesedit  a b vales performance in   vale leadership  vale  form f annual report  a b c d e f g h i j k l m n vale  form f annual report  vale across the world  a b cecilia jamasmie  february  vale posts record loss to sell core assets miningcom   vladimir basov  september  true giants of mining worlds top  iron ore mines miningcom   cvrdcontrolled carajas railway received  new sdm locomotives from electromotive diesel in december to handle growing traffic international railway journal  dead link  emd jtcwr archived  may  at the wayback machine  ferrovia centro atlântica  railway gazette mining drives african rail plans retrieved    porto e negócios  news article archived  november  at the wayback machine  brazilian mining group’s giant ore carrier soon to enter service mining weekly  may  retrieved   a b sec info  companhia vale do rio doce et al  f  for   a b a cvrd anuncia a construção de uma térmica a carvão  adriano pires o globo online  as cvrd changes name to vale iron ore pretalks begin mineweb  november    a b c vale history book chapter   vale history book chapter   a b c vale history book   alan riding  may  mining for profits in the jungles of brazil new york times   first ship loaded at ponta da madeira a special monday in vale’s history press release  january    vale taps veteran executive schvartsman as new ceo reuters  retrieved    brazil awards big mining stake to group bidding  billion new york times  may    cvrd concludes the sale of cenibra press release prnewswire  september    cvrd sells its last pulp and paper assets press release prnewswire  june 