stor is in a short position in relation to a put option at the product’s redemption as in the case of autocall products for a single asset the put option can be a european option underlying the basket of assets with the same expiry date as the final redemption date of the autocall  autocall of autoperformance considering two assets s and s the autoperformance autocall which is based on the autoperformance of two assets s vs s typically functions like a european style option with coupon payments c on each observation date in which s – s have a specific level of autoperformance called a cushion this autoperformance structure possesses an autocall tool that pays a coupon on the early redemption the product has payments on each observation date ti as follows       ret ti ret ti cushionmax j i ret ti cushioncoupon ti invst i c −≥⎡⎤⎣⎦⎡⎤…− ⎣⎦×× ×  in which reti t  si t  si   pvj da gama silva et al  the vale sa asset the vale sa product is a structured note aimed at raising international funds with a duration of at most a year launched on the new york stock exchange with an autocall price of  of the initial price coupon barrier set at  of the initial price and knockin level at  of the initial price this product’s initial price was established on  based on vale’s closing price of u  to two decimal points taken from the bloomberg database which will mature on  thus the autocall coupon barrier and knockin level prices are us  us  and us  respectively the autocall validation dates are fixed monthly as can be seen in table  table  validation dates of the asset autocall provision valuation date mandatory early redemption date april   valuation date  five business days may   valuation date  five business days june   valuation date  five business days july   valuation date  five business days august   valuation date  five business days september   valuation date  five business days october   valuation date  five business days november   valuation date  five business days december 